@NODE INTRODUCTION "Introduction to RebootWB"
    What I get annoyed about in WB is that it comes with the tools menu and the one tool ResetWB.
    I know some programs support this but it's still not used as much as it should.  It should
    have a tool that reboots Workbench as well as reseting it so I have written this small commodity
   to do this.  I puts RebootWB in the tools menu and uses lets you select if you want to reboot
   or not with a requester.  If you select Yes it performs a cold reboot. Easy as that!
@ENDNODE
@NODE FEATURES "The features of RebootWB"

     * A Information Requester to allow you to select
     * supports MagicWB and NewIcons
     * Use exchange to remove program and activate it.

@ENDNODE
@NODE INSTALLATION "How to Install RebootWB"
    Easy.  Copy RebootWB to sys:WBStartup.

@ENDNODE
@NODE USAGE "How use RebootWB"    
    The executable will be activated upon startup and sits in your tools menu.  Simply select that
    and select Yes or No.  If you select No the Requester will close.  Yes reboots WB.
@ENDNODE
